    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. that makes sense. it sounds like they're basically trying to shift all the risk onto me. are there any specific parts of that paragraph that seem especially risky or \"hidden\" that i should be looking out for? like is there anything in there that could come back to bite me unexpectedly?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The term \"negligent or more culpable act or omission\" references any wrongful behavior or failure to act, and \"recklessness or willful misconduct\" covers intentional or highly negligent actions. \"Reasonable attorneys' fees\" refer to costs of legal defense, which could add up significantly. This provision puts a lot of financial and legal pressure on you. Make sure you fully understand the services you'll be providing and ensure that you're not taking on more than you can handle or that could potentially lead to such incidents. Also, consider adding specific terms limiting what is covered under indemnification, such as not covering risks not related to your professional negligence. It might be worthwhile to negotiate caps or limitations on liabilities, and always seek legal guidance to help mitigate unforeseen implications.",
